
IE bugs :

  elm.parentNode is defined whatever if the element is inserted in the DOM or not.
  You can't use it to check if the element is inserted or not.
  
    Quick fix: check for 'elm.parentNode' and 'elm.parentNode.tagName'.

    Possible compat fixes:
      in Element.prototype.createElement, set parentNode to undefined.
      in Element.prototype.removeNode, set parentNode to undefined.


IE 8 bugs :
  
  In order to be sure to use IE8's engine (and not a compatibility view or whatever)
  you have to declare the X-UA-Compatible HTTP meta. Otherwise, expect problems.
  
  I personnaly use: <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"/>


